The paper deals with differential privacy in the context of sensitive databases and relational algebra queries, which are topics typically studied in the database (cs.DB) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a mechanism for subgraph counting, which is a problem in graph theory and falls under the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper introduces a new notion called "empirical sensitivity," which is a statistical concept and may be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses error bounds and approximation algorithms, which are topics studied in the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
